3 Amend the bill by inserting after section 3 the following:
4 'Sec. 4. Transition provisions; Housing Opportunity Program. The following
5 provisions govern the transition of the Housing Opportunity Program from the Department
6 of Economic and Community Development to the Maine Office of Community Affairs
7 established in the Maine Revised Statutes, Title 5, section 3202.
8 1. The Maine Office of Community Affairs is the successor in every way to the powers,
9 duties and functions of the Department of Economic and Community Development
10 regarding the Housing Opportunity Program.
11 2. All existing rules, regulations and procedures in effect, in operation or adopted in or
12 by the Department of Economic and Community Development regarding the Housing
13 Opportunity Program or any of its administrative units or officers are in effect and continue
14 in effect until rescinded, revised or amended by the Maine Office of Community Affairs.
15 3. All existing contracts, agreements and compacts currently in effect in the
16 Department of Economic and Community Development regarding the Housing
17 Opportunity Program continue in effect.
18 4. All records, property and equipment previously belonging to or allocated for the use
19 of the Housing Opportunity Program in the Department of Economic and Community
20 Development become, on the effective date of this Act, part of the property of the Maine
21 Office of Community Affairs.
22 5. All existing forms, licenses, letterheads and similar items bearing the name of or
23 referring to the Housing Opportunity Program may be used by the Maine Office of
24 Community Affairs until existing supplies of those items are exhausted.
25 Sec. 5. Appropriations and allocations. The following appropriations and
26 allocations are made.
